File and File Hash IOCs
File-based IOCs help identify known malware, ransomware, and other malicious files using cryptographic hashes such as MD5, SHA-1, and SHA-256.

Use Cases for File/File Hash IOCs:

Scanning attachments or downloaded files for known threats.

Enriching SIEM alerts with hash-based threat intelligence.

Investigating endpoint or network activity post-compromise.

Common Hash Lookup and Analysis Tools:

VirusTotal (https://www.virustotal.com/) â€“ Upload and analyze files or hash values against a large database of AV engines and threat intelligence sources.

Hybrid Analysis (https://www.hybrid-analysis.com) â€“ Dynamic analysis of suspicious files with detailed behavioral reports.

Malshare (https://www.malshare.com) / MalwareBazaar (https://bazaar.abuse.ch) â€“ Repositories of known malware samples and associated metadata for security research.
